==Ancient Greek==

===Pronunciation===
*παραβολή / parabolē / par-ab-ol-ay'

===Etymology===
*From [[παραβάλλω]]; a similitude (“parable”), that is, (symbolically) fictitious narrative (of common life conveying a moral), apoth gm or adage: 

===Noun===
'''παραβολή'''

# [[comparison]], [[figure]], [[parable]], [[proverb]].

